"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:4.4.5\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">4.4.5</span> 標題：小鏟子、火盆（small shovel, firepan）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מַחְתָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： machtah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:38\">EXO 25:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:3\">EXO 27:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:23\">EXO 37:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:3\">EXO 38:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:1\">LEV 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:12\">LEV 16:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:9\">NUM 4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:14\">NUM 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:6\">NUM 16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:17\">NUM 16:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:17\">NUM 16:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:17\">NUM 16:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:17\">NUM 16:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:18\">NUM 16:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num17:4\">NUM 17:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num17:11\">NUM 17:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:50\">1KI 7:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:15\">2KI 25:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:22\">2CH 4:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:19\">JER 52:19</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0005_firepan_hant.png\" alt=\"使用火盆\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">使用火盆 (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>火盆用來移動或翻動祭壇上的火炭，以及把火炭移到香壇上作其他用途（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.2.4 香壇 (incense altar)&lt;REALIA:4.2.4&gt;</a> ）。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>有學者提出，希伯來文<em>machtah</em> 也指一種特殊的容器，在清潔祭壇或搬运帳幕時用來盛聖火。因此，這是一種「貯火器」，翻譯者也可將其表述為「帶走或裝著餘燼的容器」。</p>\n<p>在上文所列的一些參考經文中，<em>machtah</em> 一詞與燒香相關聯（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:17\">NUM 16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:18\">NUM 16:18</a> ）。如果目標語言有表示「香爐」的特定詞語，這個詞就可以用在這些經文裡，但要注意避免讓人想到現代的香爐。另外，翻譯者也可以使用一個意指「火盆」的比較寬泛的詞語，因為在上文所列的大多數參考經文中，<em>machtah</em> 似乎指一種器具，用來把炭火移到另一個地方，並且有時會把香放在炭火上面。另參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.2.4 香壇 (incense altar)&lt;REALIA:4.2.4&gt;</a> 和<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.4.7 香爐(censer)&lt;REALIA:4.4.7&gt;</a> 。</p>\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0454_firepan.jpg\" alt=\"青銅火盆或香鏟（羅馬，公元1世紀晚期至2世紀早期）\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">青銅火盆或香鏟（羅馬，公元1世紀晚期至2世紀早期） (Metropolitan Museum of Art, CC0, MMA)</figcaption></figure>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:38\">EXO 25:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:23\">EXO 37:23</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:9\">NUM 4:9</a> 中，<em>machtah</em> 與燈臺相關聯（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.3.4 燈臺 (lampstand, menorah)&lt;REALIA:4.3.4&gt;</a> ），有些譯本仍然將其譯作「火盆」（“firepans”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jewish Publication Society Version\">NJPSV</abbr> ），然而也有譯本譯作「托盤」（“trays”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> ）。無論哪種譯法，<em>machtah</em> 對於燈臺有何用處並不清楚。這裡描述和繪出的物品可能有多種用途。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
